  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>Located in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/f6cb1f0178b7447488bbf36b5f109fbc" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f6cb1f0178b7447488bbf36b5f109fbc}" title="Grindelwald">Grindelwald</a>, the family owned </span><span>Jungfrau Lodge is a small, comfortable hotel offering good value, simple accommodation and a friendly atmosphere. Most of our rooms are south-facing, enjoying lovely views of Mount Eiger and surrounding mountains. For outdoor enthusiasts, Hotel Jungfrau Lodge offers easy access to an array of activities. Whether it's winter walking, skiing, snowboarding, or sight-seeing, the lodge's location is a gateway to a variety of adventures in the <a data-udi="umb://document/52fab17731fa49639f8a0841e064a064" href="/{localLink:umb://document/52fab17731fa49639f8a0841e064a064}" title="Switzerland">Swiss Alps</a>.</span></p>
<h2><span>Excellent location</span></h2>
<p>The lodge has an ideal location – you are relatively close to the resort amenities including the train station, shops and restaurants, as well as a bus ride to the main ski lifts. Head up the First mountain for a day of adventures, enjoys skiing, tobogganing, incredible views from the First Cliff Walk (weather permitting) or fly through the air at up to 50mph on the First Flieger or Glider. You are also a short distance from the Grindelwald Terminal, giving you access to the fantastic Jungfrau Ski Region, including <a data-udi="umb://document/7e163ac5c9114f0dae9f3f8d222fa730" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7e163ac5c9114f0dae9f3f8d222fa730}" title="Wengen">Wengen</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/c494e0deab1140028dfcdd140d9451cc" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c494e0deab1140028dfcdd140d9451cc}" title="Murren">Mürren</a>.</p>
<h2><span>Eiger views</span></h2>
<p>Set across the main building and the Annex Crystal, you can choose from a variety of room options to suit your needs. Hotel Jungfrau Lodge offers comfortable rooms, and each decorated in a simplistic style, offering great value accommodation in the centre of Grindelwald. Plus, many of the rooms benefit from having views of the iconic Eiger mountain. Whether you're traveling solo, as a couple, or with family, you'll find a room to suit your needs here.</p>]]></description>
